<h2 class="nounderline">Children&rsquo;s Mental Health and Emotional Behavorial Disorder Specialist</h2>

<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Children&rsquo;s Mental Health and Emotional Behavioral Disorder (EBD) Specialist<br />
<strong>SUPERVISOR</strong>: Renelle Nelson<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: Full time with option for PT at 75%, Salaried Monthly, Exempt status
</p>
<h3>RESPONSIBILITIES/ROLES</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Provide individual assistance, information, and guidance to parents through phone, email, and web conferencing regarding mental health issues and emotional behavioral disorders for children and youth. </li>
    <li>Assist families at occasional meetings&mdash;in person or through technology&mdash;to develop plans for child and youth learning and development.</li>
    <li>Help lead a peer to peer support initiative for families of children and youth with mental health issues and emotional behavioral disorders.</li>
    <li>Write materials to support families of children and youth with mental health issues and emotional behavioral disorders including articles and handouts.</li>
    <li>Contribute information about program activities on PACER's website.</li>
    <li>Assist with a parent leadership summit to build capacity for parental involvement in mental health policy issues.</li>
    <li>Assist in public information dissemination and educational activities with presentations to various organizations and professional groups.</li>
    <li>Collect program data.</li>
    <li>Assist with other activities as needed.</li>
</ul>

<h3>EXPERIENCE/BACKGROUND SKILLS</h3>
<ol>
	<li>College degree or equivalent background gained through training or work experience</li>
    <li>Ability to work well with others </li>
    <li>Interest in relating to families of children and youth with mental health issues and emotional behavioral disorders</li>
    <li>Experience in giving presentations and assisting others on the telephone</li>
    <li>Experience working with individuals in a guidance or counseling role</li>
    <li>Knowledge of, or ability to learn about, laws and rules related to education and community resources for children and youth with mental health issues and emotional behavioral disorders</li>
    <li>Ability to keep good records, collect data, and enter information into electronic databases for evaluation purposes</li>
    <li>Working knowledge of Microsoft Word, PowerPoint and Outlook </li>
    <li>Ability to provide own transportation and flexibility to travel. </li>
    <li>Ability to work with diverse populations</li>
    <li>Ability to apply analytical skills</li>
    <li>Excellent organizational skills and ability to meet deadlines</li>
</ol>


<p>
Salary to be determined based on experience. Position available immediately.<br />
Parents of children with disabilities  are encouraged to apply.</p>

